<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-098-882  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 098 882.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  March 6 1989 v8 n5 p40(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Pub. Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Apollo gets pact for a classified FDDI network. (Fiber DistributedData Interface) (Apollo Computer Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Masud, S.A.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apollo Computer Inc. (contracts).andO;Ticker:    APCI.andO;Topic:     Fiber Distributed Data Interface StandardFiber OpticsConnectivityGovernment ContractsNetworks.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Apollo Gets Pact For a Classified FDDI NetworkandM;Apollo Computer Inc. has announced it has received a classified sole-sourcecontract to develop and install a fiber-optic network based on the FiberDistributed Data Interface standard (FDDI).andM;FDDI is for a network using an optical fiber-ring topology that supports datatransfers on each ring at up to 100 megabits/sec.andM;Apollo spokesman Mark Lederhos said the network will link a minimum of threof Apollo's new Series 1000 Personal Super-computers, which will be able totake advantage of the FDDI local area network's high bandwidth.andP;  One of thethree workstations will be used as a gateway to much slower Ethernet andtoken-ring LANs, Lederhos said.andM;Under the contract, Apollo, among other items, will supply FDDI cards for theworkstations and its Station Management (SMT) software.andP;  SMT if FDDI softwarethat allows controllers on the network to communicate and track networkevents.andM;Apollo also will be supplying its embedded Network Computing System, atechnology that allows distributed use of unused processor cycles ofcomputers on a network.andP;  Apollo is to deliver the FDDI network in the fall,Lederhos said.andO;</TEXT></DOC>